&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48370368"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48370368&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Points: 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48370368</guid><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 14:00:38 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: LocalFlow – AI data analysis where the LLM never sees your data</title><link>https://github.com/localflow-ai/localflow-core</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi HN, I'm the author of the JSweet project (Java-to-TypeScript transpiler), but today I'd like to show you something new: LocalFlow.&lt;p&gt;There are two common ways to analyse your data with AI ("Talk to your Data"):
1. Use powerful frontier models on the cloud — but hand over your data and pay per token
2. Use on-premise or local models — but accept weaker results and significant hardware costs&lt;p&gt;LocalFlow proposes a third approach I call "metadata-first AI": send only the schema to the LLM (column names, types, a few stats — never the actual values), and ask it to generate code that runs locally on your full dataset (scale it to millions of rows at zero additional token cost).&lt;p&gt;I'm curious what you think :)&lt;p&gt;Live demo (drop in any CSV): &lt;a href="https://apps.localflow.fr/demo/" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://apps.localflow.fr/demo/&lt;/a&gt;
GitHub: &lt;a href="https://github.com/localflow-ai/localflow-core" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://github.com/localflow-ai/localflow-core&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
